<h1>Problem 1706 - 2016 IMOSL, G6, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 8</h2>
<p>Let \(ABCD\) be a convex quadrilateral with \(\angle ABC = \angle ADC < 90^{\circ}\). The internal angle bisectors of \(\angle ABC\) and \(\angle ADC\) meet \(AC\) at \(E\) and \(F\) respectively, and meet each other at point \(P\). Let \(M\) be the midpoint of \(AC\) and let \(\omega\) be the circumcircle of triangle \(BPD\). Segments \(BM\) and \(DM\) intersect \(\omega\) again at \(X\) and \(Y\) respectively. Denote by \(Q\) the intersection point of lines \(XE\) and \(YF\). Prove that \(PQ \perp AC\).</p>
